items.title: David Walliams denies inappropriate behaviour after publisher drops him
items.standfirst: British children's author and comedian David Walliams has denied allegations of inappropriate behaviour after publisher HarperCollins dropped him.
items.content: British children's author and comedian David Walliams has denied allegations of inappropriate behaviour after publisher HarperCollins dropped him.Walliams, 54, is one of the UK's bestselling children's book authors and a former judge on the TV show Britain's Got Talent.In a statement on Friday, HarperCollins said: "After careful consideration, and under the leadership of its new CEO, HarperCollins UK has decided not to publish any new titles by David Walliams. The author is aware of this decision."READ MORE: Clinton looms large in Epstein files, but no sign of Trump A spokesperson for Walliams said in a statement that he "has never been informed of any allegations raised against him by HarperCollins.""He was not party to any investigation or given any opportunity to answer questions. David strongly denies that he has behaved inappropriately and is taking legal advice," the statement said.The publisher said it would not comment on internal matters, "to respect the privacy of individuals."READ MORE: Brave little boy receives early Christmas surprise after reaching medical milestone "HarperCollins takes employee wellbeing extremely seriously and has processes in place for reporting and investigating concerns," it said.Walliams has published over 40 children's books and sold more than 60 million copies worldwide, according to his website. Several of them, including Gangsta Granny, have been adapted into a BBC comedy dramas and stage productions.Walliams left his role as judge on Britain's Got Talent in 2022 after apologising for making "disrespectful comments" about auditioning contestants.DOWNLOAD THE 9NEWS APP: Stay across all the latest in breaking news, sport, politics and the weather via our news app and get notifications sent straight to your smartphone.
